                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270405-70-off395 t18270405-70-crimeloc398"></join>. On the 19th of February, about eight o'clock in the evening, this flannel stood at my door, tied up in different lengths - it was within the door; I was at the bottom of the shop, and saw the top-piece drawn out. I ran out, and saw the prisoner putting it under his apron; I called stop thief! and he dropped the flannel just before the watchman stopped him.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
